SNP: rare, but other GW-sig signal at Locus

column2: In “Locus” set of columns, the “Locus/Gene” column refers to the published locus name. All positions are NCBI build 37 (hg19). In the “Known SNP” set of columns, the “PMID” column provides the reference for the corresponding publication. The “Known SNP results” columns provides results for the exact SNP; the “Rsq08-BestSNP” columns provides results for the SNP with minimum p-value across all BP traits, amongst all proxy SNPs in Linkage Disequilibrium (r2 ≥ 0.8); the “Rsq01-Locus-BestSNP” columns provides results for the SNP with minimum p-value across all BP traits amongst all SNPs within the locus ±500kb from the known SNP and in Linkage Disequilibrium (r2 ≥ 0.1). All association results are from the GWAS discovery meta-analysis. “Trait” corresponds to the BP trait with minimum p-value (“P_min”). The TRUE/FALSE columns for “GWsig”, “Bonf”, “sig01” indicate whether the corresponding SNP reaches P < 5×10-8, P < 0.05/274, or P < 0.01, respectively. If the known SNP itself is not available within the MAF≥1% HRC-imputed data, “n/a” is indicated. If subsequent columns would correspond to the same best SNP from the previous set of columns, the cells are left blank. The "Coverage" column provides extra information for the 28 SNPs which were not covered exactly within the MAF≥1% HRC-imputed data; SBP: systolic blood pressure; DBP: diastolic blood pressure; PP: pulse pressure
